parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank overflow can cause gasoline to spill onto the vehicle, ground, and person filling the tank, creating a fire hazard and potential for serious injury.
symptoms: Gasoline spills out of the fuel tank filler neck when the tank is filled to capacity
even when the pump shuts off automatically. The spill can occur suddenly
soaking the person filling the tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of replacement parts for the Takata airbag recall can lead to a prolonged risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the faulty airbag inflators may rupture and cause metal fragments to strike vehicle occupants.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the recall repair process rather than a specific symptom experienced by vehicle owners.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion can cause the airbags to malfunction, leading to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Water intrusion causing the airbags to get wet
and passenger front airbag possibly compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clock Spring and Control Module Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring and control module can cause the airbag warning indicator to illuminate, which can lead to a failure of the airbag system in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: wires burned to the control module

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank overflow/fuel spitting back issue can cause a hazardous situation, potentially leading to fires, explosions, or environmental damage. The sudden release of fuel can also cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel spits back out of the tank when filling up
fuel sprays onto the vehicle and the person filling up
fuel gushes out of the tank after the pump shuts off
